ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT /*+ ORDERED USE_NL(FF_RRAS) PARALLEL(RNT_AGRS,4) */ FF_RRAS.RES_RES_NBR, FF_RRAS.TPR_PGM_ID FROM GWYDB.RNT_AGRS,GWYDB.FF_RRAS WHERE FF_RRAS.RES_RES_NBR = RNT_AGRS.RES_RES_NBR AND (RNT_AGRS.CO_TMSP >= TRUNC(SYSDATE- 2) OR RNT_AGRS.ACTL_CO_STRT_TMSP >= TRUNC(SYSDATE-2)) AND trim(FF_RRAS.tpr_pgm_id) is not null and FF_RRAS.tpr_pgm_id is not null union SELECT FF_RRAS2.RES_RES_NBR, FF_RRAS2.TPR_PGM_ID FROM GWYDB.FF_RRAS FF_RRAS2 JOIN COGRPT.RES2_FF ON RES2_FF.RES_NBR=FF_RRAS2.RES_RES_NBR WHERE trim(FF_RRAS2.tpr_pgm_id) is not null

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT /*+ FIRST_ROWS PARALLEL(RES,10) */FF_RRAS.RES_RES_NBR, FF_RRAS.TPR_PGM_ID FROM GWYDB.FF_RRAS, GWYDB.RES WHERE FF_RRAS.RES_RES_NBR = RES.RES_NBR AND (( RES.RES_TMSP >=(TRUNC($$ODY_SYSDATE_GE) -2) OR RES.LST_CHNG_DT >= (TRUNC($$ODY_SYSDATE_GE) - 2)) OR RES.RES_STAT = 'NS' AND RES.PROJ_CO_TMSP >= TRUNC($$ODY_SYSDATE_GE- 10)) AND RES.FF_FLG = 'Y' AND trim(FF_RRAS.tpr_pgm_id) is not null and FF_RRAS.tpr_pgm_id is not null

ATTRIBUTE.NAME: Sql Query
ATTRIBUTE.VALUE: SELECT /*+ ORDERED USE_NL(FF_RRAS) PARALLEL(RNT_AGRS,4) */ FF_RRAS.RES_RES_NBR, FF_RRAS.TPR_PGM_ID FROM GWYDB.RNT_AGRS,GWYDB.FF_RRAS WHERE FF_RRAS.RES_RES_NBR = RNT_AGRS.RES_RES_NBR AND rnt_agr_stat = 'CA' AND ACTL_CI_TMSP >= TRUNC($$ODY_SYSDATE_GE) -2 AND trim(FF_RRAS.tpr_pgm_id) is not null and FF_RRAS.tpr_pgm_id is not null

SOURCE.DESCRIPTION: Odyssey main rental agreement table. It's the header table for all rental agreement transactions for Odyssey.
SOURCE.NAME: RNT_AGRS

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
Rental Agreement number. This number identifies the rental agreement. This column indicates a unique rental agreement number used to identify the rental. This rental could be in any state as defined by the REA.RNT_AGR_STAT.
Set: This field gets set only once with the rental agreement number of the rental.
Update: No possibility of update once it is set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: RNT_AGR_NBR

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Unix ID of the user that created the rental agreement.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CREAT_BY

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column belongs to the RNT_AGRS (REA) table. This timestamp captures the timestamp the vehicle is supposedly due to return. It may during the life of the rental based on the renter. Normally it will match the RNT_AGRS.CI_TMSP.
Set: This timestamp is set with the information entered on the rental agreement when it is first committed to the database.
Update: Each time a change is reported by the renter, this field is updated and so is the CI_TMSP. However on final check in, this field may not match and is not updated. Only the CI_TMSP is updated.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: DUE_CI_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
Defined as indicative of the source of a rental agreement. It could take on the following values: Reservation (RS), Walk-ins (WI), Manual (MA), and Non-Revenue (NR). This column used in conjunction with the REA.RNT_AGR_STAT column clearly indicates whether the vehicle is rented as a Revenue movement (RS, WI, MA) or as a Non-Revenue movement (NR). Therefore all MA manual entries are representative of Revenue movements.
Set: This field is set once with the type of rental being performed. Reservation, Walk-in, Manual, or a Non-Revenue movement.
Update: Not updated once set. Possible values: RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_SRC_CD MA Manual Agreement RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_SRC_CD RS Reservation RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_SRC_CD NR Non Revenue RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_SRC_CD WI Walk In
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: RNT_AGR_SRC_CD

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
Defined as indicative of the current state of the rental. It could take on the following values: Cancelled (CA), Check-in (CI), Invoiced (IN), Not Complete (NC), or Open (OP). A rental agreement cannot be invoiced before it is checked-in and the rental is in NC or OP state if the rental is currently in progress. Canceled Rental Agreements are those rentals that never took place.
Set: This field gets set with the current status of the rental agreement.
Update: Everytime the status of the rental agreement changes this field gets updated. Possible values: RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_STAT RN RENTAL AGREEMENT WITH NO CAR RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_STAT OP Open RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_STAT IN Invoiced RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_STAT CI Check In RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_STAT CA Cancelled RNT_AGRS.RNT_AGR_STAT NC Incomplete
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: RNT_AGR_STAT

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
Defined as the Actual time at which the rental agreement was updated to indicate that the vehicle was checked in. This timestamp may differ from the physical time at which the vehicle was checked in to the VHCL_MVS table. This timestamp is mainly used for auditing purposes but is our only source of identifying backdated rentals. A twist to this timestamp is when a completed rental can be reopened before billing picks up the entry. If billing does pick it up the RNT_AGR_INV_NOTES.BTCH_PROC_ID will be set to the timestamp the entry was billed or it will be NULL. (Pending CIR for June 1999).
Set: This timestamp gets set when the last vehicle (movement against the rental) is entered into the system as checked in (committed). It gets populated with the local timestamp of the users default station closing out the rental agreement.
Update: Updated on Rental Modification, Complete Checkin, Cancellation, and Incomplete Checkin.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: ACTL_CI_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This timestamp defines the time at which the rental agreement transaction was committed to the database. In the case of regular rentals, this timestamp will closely match the REA.CO_TMSP but it would differ in the case of a Manual rental. Since the Manual rental is normally used to identify backdated rentals, the ACTL_CO_END_TMSP coupled with the REA.RNT_AGR_SRC_CD is the only measure we have available to identify these types of rental agreements. This timestamp is mainly used for auditing purposes but is our only source of identifying backdated rental.
Set: Gets set when the rental agreement is committed to the database with the local timestamp of the users default station who is entering in the rental agreement.
Update: Not updated once set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: ACTL_CO_END_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This timestamp defines the time the rental agreement transaction was started. This timestamp would differ from the CO_TMSP since it shows an in-process entry into RNT_AGRS. This timestamp is mainly used for auditing purposes but is our only source of identifying backdated rentals.
Set: Gets set the first time a new rental agreement transaction is started with the local timestamp of the users default station entering in the rental information.
Update: Not updated once set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: ACTL_CO_STRT_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Cancel Reason Code. 2 digit reason code that tells the reason of cancellation. RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD ER Error RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD CT Customer Turndown RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD WA Could not wait RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD RA Found better rate RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD RV Refused Vehicle RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD PP Pre-printed no-show RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD VN Vehicle not needed RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD PR Promotion not accepted RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD OD Odyssey testing RNT_AGRS.CANCEL_RSN_CD OT Other
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CANCEL_RSN_CD

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Free form text field that describes a cancelation reason.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CANCEL_TXT

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Indicates whether or not to print future invoice adjustments for credit card charge backs.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CHG_BACK_FLG

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
The charge timestamps describe the amount of time a patron is charged for using a vehicle on a rental agreement. This timestamp identifies the end of the charge time on a rented vehicle. This timestamp should be the same as the RNT_AGRS.CI_TMSP even for non revenue movements.
Set: This timestamp gets set manually after the rental is closed with the local timestamp of the users default station setting the Charge check in time.
Update: Manual updates to this field are possible.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CHG_CI_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
The charge timestamps describe the amount of time a patron is charged for using a vehicle on a rental agreement. This timestamp identifies the start of the charge time on a rented vehicle.
Set: This timestamp gets set manually after a rental is created with the local timestamp of the users default station setting the Charge checkout time. This timestamp should be the same as the RNT_AGRS.ORIG_CO_TMSP even for Non revenue movements.
Update: Manual updates to this field are possible.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CHG_CO_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: ANC employee that took the checked in car.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CI_BY

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This timestamp identifies when a vehicle in the REA table, revenue or non-revenue, was physically checked in. This timestamp could also be used as the REA.ACTL_CI_TMSP except in the case of backdated rentals. This timestamp must be populated at all times except when the status of the rental agreement is Canceled, or Open. Set: This timestamp gets populated the first time a vehicle is attached to a rental agreement with the local time of the users default station attaching the vehicle. It is normally set with the ORIG_CI_TMSP.
Update: Updated once a vehicle is physically checked back in or on other rental agreement modifications with the local time of the users default station. If there are vehicle exchanges this field does not reflect it. It only captures the last timestamp before the rental agreement is closed.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CI_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Primary contract id for a rental.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CON_CON_ID_PRIM

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Coupon Id #1. There can be 3 different coupons for a rental agreement.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: COUPON_1_ID

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Quantity of coupons for Coupon 1.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: COUPON_1_QTY

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Coupon Id #2. There can be 3 different coupons for a rental agreement.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: COUPON_2_ID

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Quantity of coupons for Coupon 2.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: COUPON_2_QTY

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Coupon Id #3. There can be 3 different coupons for a rental agreement.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: COUPON_3_ID

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Quantity of coupons for Coupon 3.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: COUPON_3_QTY

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This timestamp identifies when a vehicle in the REA table, revenue or non-revenue, was physically checked out. This timestamp could also be used as the ACTL_CO_STRT_TMSP except in the case of backdated rentals or cancellations. This timestamp should be populated at all times if a rental agreement is not in Canceled status. This timestamp is not related to vehicles.
Set: This timestamp gets populated the first time a vehicle gets assigned to the rental agreement with the local time of the users default station initiating the checkout. It is normally set with the ORIG_CO_TMSP.
Update: Not updated once set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CO_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This timestamp identifies when the vehicle is due back once a rental is created. This field is only updated once a vehicle is associated to the rental. After that the CI_TMSP must be relied upon.
Set: When a rental agreement is created, this field gets populated with the scheduled time stamp the vehicle on the rental agreement is due back. This should only get set once a vehicle is assigned to the rental agreement.
Update: Updated with the scheduled time entered once an associated vehicle is checked out on the rental agreement. No further updates take place.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: ORIG_CI_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This timestamp identifies when the vehicle is to be checked out on the rental agreement. This field is only updated once a vehicle is associated to the rental. After that the CO_TMSP must be relied upon.
Set: When a rental agreement is created, this field gets populated with the scheduled timestamp the vehicle will be checked out. This should only get set once a vehicle is assigned to the rental agreement.
Update: Not updated once set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: ORIG_CO_TMSP

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column stores the Station ID where the user was defaulted to when the rental agreement was closed. This field is used mainly for auditing and must not be used for most queries unless they are auditing related.
Set: This field gets populated with the station id that updates the rental agreement with check in information and closed it. It gets populated with the station id of the station the user is defaulted to on check in.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: STA_STN_ID_ACTL_CI

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column stores the Station ID where the user was defaulted to when the rental agreement was created. This field is used mainly for auditing and must not be used for most queries unless they are auditing related.
Set: This field gets populated with the station id where the rental agreement was created. It may differ from the station where the vehicle gets physically checked out from.
Update: Not updated once set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: STA_STN_ID_ACTL_CO

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column identifies the station id where the last vehicle on the same rental agreement was physically checked-in to at the end of the rental. It should match the REA.STA_STN_ID_ORIG_CI.
Set: This field gets set with the station id where the last vehicle on a rental agreement gets physically checked in.
Update: Updated on modification, returns, cancellations and incomplete returns.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: STA_STN_ID_CHK_IN

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column plays a part in vehicle exchanges on a rental agreement. It identifies the last station id that modified this rental agreement.
Set: This field gets set with the station id that last modified this Rental Agreement.
Update: Changes on the next modification/update.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: STA_STN_ID_LST_CHNG

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column identifies the original station id where the vehicle was scheduled to be returned to.
Set: This field gets set with the station id where the vehicle on a rental agreement is scheduled to be checked into last. This station id may differ from the station id the vehicle is physically checked into.
Update: Updated on rental agreement modification.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: STA_STN_ID_ORIG_CI

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION:
This column identifies the original station id where the vehicle was scheduled to be checked out from first. This is the first station id populated when a vehicle is expected to leave the rental lot.
Set: This field gets set with the station id where the vehicle on a rental agreement is scheduled to be checked out from first. This station id may differ from the station id where the vehicle gets physically checked out from. The only place to find this is in the vehicle moves table.
Update: Not updated once set.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: STA_STN_ID_ORIG_CO

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Number of days of charges. Charge Days.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: CHARGE_DAYS_NBR

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This will allow for auditing of transactions, minimizing the amount of time to determine problems with rental transactions.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: AUDIT_NOTE_ID

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Upsell amount associated with this rental.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: UPSELL_REV_AMT

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: Brand Code. ZL = National. AL = Alamo.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: BRN_BRAND_ID

SOURCEFIELD.DESCRIPTION: This field does not exist on the RNT_AGRS table, it is put there as a source to be queried using the function GWYDB.FN_RPT_GET_NOTES(NTE_NOTE_ID). this will return the first 2000 characters of any comment associated to this rental.
SOURCEFIELD.NAME: RENTAL_NOTES

SOURCEFIELD.NAME: AUDIT_NOTES
